    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1939-05-18T16:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1939-05-18T16:00:00-05:00" n="131"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d131">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.102 Kulangsu/134: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Consul at Amoy</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">MacVitty</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1939-05-18T17:00:00-04:00"
                            >May 18, 1939—5 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>13. Department’s 12, May 17, 7 p.m., and previous. With reference to the demands
                    presented by the Japanese authorities to the Municipal Council mentioned in your
                    21, May 15, 11 a.m., there is quoted below for your confidential information and
                    guidance pertinent portions of a telegram sent on January 11, 1938, to the
                    Consul General at Shanghai containing broad views for the consideration of <pb
                        facs="0120" n="114" xml:id="pg_114"/> the Consul General in connection with
                    the situation with which the Municipal Council of the International Settlement
                    at Shanghai was then being confronted.</p>
                <p>[Here follows quotation from telegram under reference, printed in <ref
                        target="frus1938v04#pg_119">
                        <hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, 1938, volume IV, page
                    119</ref>.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
